DENT INFORMATION NEEDS AND LIBRARY USER EDUCATION.     A SMALL GROUP OF POLYTECHNIC UNDERGRADUATES WERE INTERVIEWED OVER A 6 WEEKPERIOD IN ORDER TO INVESTIGATE THEIR INFORMATION NEEDS AND THEIR APPROACHES TOMEETING THEM. ACADEMIC STAFF WERE THEN INTERVIEWED TO DISCOVER THEIRPERCEPTION OF THE STUDENTS' INFORMATION REQUIREMENTS. THE FINDINGS ARESUMMARISED WITH PARTICULAR REFERENCE TO THE ROLE OF LIBRARIES IN SOLVING THESTUDENTS' INFORMATION NEEDS. THE RELEVANCE OF THE FINDINGS TO THE PLANNING OFLIBRARY USER EDUCATION PROGRAMMES ARE DISCUSSED